        </p>
      </introduction>

      <task>
        <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>a \in \Z</m> and let <m>k \in \Z</m> with <m>k \ne 0</m>.
          Prove that if <m>k \mid a</m> and <m>k \mid \left( {a + 1} \right)</m>,
          then <m>k \mid 1</m>, and hence <m>k = \pm 1</m>.
        </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
          <p>
            Prove that <m>k \mid \left[ ( {a+1} ) - a \right]</m>.
          </p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <p>
          Let <m>a \in \mathbb{Z}</m>.
          Find the greatest common divisor of the consecutive integers <m>a</m> and <m>a + 1</m>.
          That is, determine <m>\gcd( {a, a + 1} )</m>.
        </p>
      </task>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
